<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  AccessibilityService declaration.
  Reference: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/accessibilityservice/AccessibilityServiceInfo

  typeWindowStateChanged  — foreground app/window changed (the app-switch signal)
  typeWindowContentChanged — content within the current window changed
  typeViewScrolled        — user scrolled; new content entered the viewport

  ScanGate debounces the last two, which fire far faster than a scan is useful.

  isAccessibilityTool — the fix for backlog item 1(b), and the only one there is.
  Android 14 (API 34) added accessibilityDataSensitive: a view marked sensitive is
  served to accessibility services that declare isAccessibilityTool and withheld
  from every other one. Settings marks the device-admin list rows that way, which
  is why that screen harvested chrome and no rows while a uiautomator dump of the
  same moment showed them — UiAutomation is exempt. Measured on an android-36
  emulator: without this the RecyclerView reports childCount=0 and refresh() does
  not change it; with it, 2 children and the SELF_IN_SETTINGS catch-all fires.

  Neither candidate the backlog ranked above this one survived the measurement:
  flagIncludeNotImportantViews grew the tree 5 -> 16 nodes without producing a
  single row, and is deliberately not set here.

  This is also a Play policy declaration — it asserts the service is built to
  assist users with disabilities — so it is a distribution commitment, not just a
  manifest attribute. Accepted knowingly: short of Device Owner, which plan.md §7
  rules out permanently, nothing else reaches those rows.

  References:
    https://developer.android.com/reference/android/R.attr#accessibilityDataSensitive
    https://developer.android.com/reference/android/accessibilityservice/AccessibilityServiceInfo#isAccessibilityTool()
-->
<accessibility-service xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:accessibilityEventTypes="typeWindowStateChanged|typeWindowContentChanged|typeViewScrolled"
    android:accessibilityFeedbackType="feedbackGeneric"
    android:accessibilityFlags="flagReportViewIds|flagRetrieveInteractiveWindows"
    android:canRetrieveWindowContent="true"
    android:isAccessibilityTool="true"
    android:description="@string/accessibility_service_description"
    android:notificationTimeout="100" />
